snippet.title: Cyber Knight
snippet.description:
When I am found to be deceased and unable to continue the Minesweeper Let's Play series, anyone else is allowed to continue the series on their own channel so long as they follow the proper format of the series. 

- Each episode must have the title "Let's Play Minesweeper - Episode (N of previous episode + 1)" regardless of whether the English language and modern counting system have changed or gone extinct. 
- Each episode must be roughly ten minutes in length. 
- Each episode must be a 2-dimensional recording of the game Minesweeper. No live events, holographic recordings, etc.
- This exact text must be copied and pasted on one's about page (or equivalent on another website) if they take up the mantle.
- One video shall be uploaded per day (24 hours). If you miss a day, keep a log of missed episodes and upload multiple later.
- The series is not allowed to end.

snippet.title: deeboi70
snippet.description:
I AM NOT LIMMY, This is an unofficial Limmy's Show page.
This all started one night when I quickly came home from a party for something and had a few minutes to spare so I put the TV on and I seen Limmy's Show was about to start and as soon as I flicked the channel all I heard was, "Fuckin' ah wiz in ma kitchen right, checkin' tae see if ma t-shirt wiz dry right" (Translation - "Fucking, I was in my kitchen, right, checking to see if my t-shirt was dry, right") It was my first encounter with Dee Dee, and I was like, WTF who is this? , why have I never seen this before? who is he?
I later went back to the party and was telling everyone about the guy Dee Dee and no-one had heard of or seen it before either and there was no clips of Dee Dee on you tube yet so the day after I uploaded Dee Dee In The Kitchen and sent people links to watch it, and before I knew it people were subscribing and asking for more videos and it just evolved until I had all the clips I could possibly find.

snippet.title: Dr Brian Keating
snippet.description:
🧠The Universe’s Brightest Minds Are Here!🧠 
Every week you'll get long-form interviews with a brilliant scientist, or a short, fun deep-dive into cutting-edge physics and astronomy experiments.

I'm the Chancellor's Distinguished Professor of Physics at UC San Diego where my team & I study the origin & evolution of space, time, & matter. 

Scientists are obligated to explain their work in simple terms to non-experts. I think scientifically and I want you to too.

I’ve been a professor for 19 years and wrote INTO THE IMPOSSIBLE & LOSING THE NOBEL PRIZE = a 'Best Science Book' at Science Friday and one of the best non-fiction books of all time according to Amazon.

I'm on a mission to magnify curiosity, stoke imagination, & inspire minds of all ages.
